Imagery Description: (a) Nude youth with fillet in right hand and phiale in left, draped woman with fillet and mirror, (b) seated halfNon Sepcifieddraped woman (cf. no. 977) with phiale and wreath in right hand, knotty stick in left. The lid is in three elements, of which the two lekanis lids are decorated with tongues and the third, a lebes gamikos, with female heads.
